Command every repository as one fleet.

Usage: gitfleet [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  access       Organization access management
  advisory     Security advisory operations
  alias        Command aliases
  analytics    Repository and pipeline analytics
  api          Raw provider API access
  attestation  Attestation operations
  auth         Provider authentication and profiles
  browse       Browse repository resources
  change       Proposed changes and merge operations
  code         Code navigation and search
  completion   Shell completion generation
  config       Configuration management
  deps         Dependency review and analysis
  deploy       Deployment management
  dev          Development environments
  discussion   Discussion management
  environment  Environment management
  govern       Repository ruleset governance
  identity     Account keys (SSH, GPG)
  inbox        Notification management
  issue        Issue management
  label        Label management
  license      License discovery
  planning     Planning boards, milestones, and projects
  pipeline     CI/CD pipeline definitions and runs
  policy       Repository protection policies
  registry     Package registry
  release      Release management
  repo         Repository lifecycle and forks
  review       Reviews, comments, and reactions
  runner       CI/CD runner management
  search       Search repositories and code
  secret       Repository secrets
  security     Security advisories and scanning
  site         Repository pages
  snippet      Hosted snippets
  template     Repository templates
  variable     Repository variables
  version      Version information
  webhook      Webhook management
  wiki         Repository wiki pages
  workspace    Named fleets and multi-repository execution
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --json           
      --debug          
      --theme <THEME>  [default: auto]
      --yes            
      --dry-run        
  -h, --help           Print help
  -V, --version        Print version
